 - [sighs] She and Justin, um--
     they knew each other.

10:38.305 --> 10:40.672
    Looks like there's maybe
         20 phone calls

10:40.674 --> 10:43.074
and twice as many texts between
  the two of them last month.

10:43.076 --> 10:45.710
The last phone call she made
was a half hour

10:45.712 --> 10:47.812
before time of death.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.914
    - He said he was in town
       to help a friend.

10:49.916 --> 10:50.949
       Maybe it was her.

10:50.951 --> 10:52.117
     - Where is Justin now?

10:52.119 --> 10:54.052
          - He should be at home
          with Olive and Daniel.

10:54.054 --> 10:55.787
           - Did he ever mention
               this girl to you?

10:55.789 --> 10:59.024
  - Don't you think I would've
    mentioned it if he did?

10:59.026 --> 11:01.793
           <i>[dark music]</i>

11:01.795 --> 11:04.062
     Straight to voicemail.

11:04.064 --> 11:06.798
               <i>â™ª </i>

11:06.800 --> 11:08.166
                 Where's Justin?

11:08.168 --> 11:09.901
- He left over an hour ago.

11:09.903 --> 11:13.271
 - Have you tried calling him?
     - He's not answering.

11:13.273 --> 11:14.439
       I texted him too.

11:14.441 --> 11:16.274
       Hank, I'm worried.

11:16.276 --> 11:19.244
               - We'll find him.

11:19.246 --> 11:22.414
    - Mouse, I need you to track
       the GPS on Justin's car--

11:22.416 --> 11:24.082
                            now.

11:24.084 --> 11:27.085
       <i>[suspenseful music]</i>

11:27.087 --> 11:33.992
               <i>â™ª </i>

11:33.994 --> 11:35.226
                      Turn here.

11:35.228 --> 11:38.096
               <i>â™ª </i>

11:38.098 --> 11:39.964
- There it is.

